<paragraph id="589915546BDC7272CDB0C99158E10953" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName id="2B4DE7C086370CBD484543AACBBA1444" authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" status="stat. nov.">Basionym: Collospermum</taxonomicName>
Skottsb., Kongl. Svenska Vetensk. Acad. Handl. Ser. 3, 14(2): 72. 1934. Type: 
<taxonomicName id="8D30C7DD77C3FFAF9FA79F1A9635B8FE" authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum hastatum" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hastatum" status="stat. nov.">
<emphasis id="F8F9C658E383230FB2A5ACF2C0251C57" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Collospermum hastatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Colenso) Skottsb. [Lectotypified by 
<bibRefCitation id="A21B8BF43B67AA14C2688D2660028B13" author="Moore, LB" journalOrPublisher="Flora of New Zealand. Indigenous Tracheophyta: Monocotyledones except Gramineae" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" refId="B20" refString="Moore, LB, Edgar, E, 1976. . Flora of New Zealand. Indigenous Tracheophyta: Monocotyledones except Gramineae Vol. 2" volume="Vol. 2" year="1976">Moore and Edgar (1976)</bibRefCitation>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9ED51360D465CA82E83FBA1897A2427E" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="note">
<paragraph id="5B6D7CFC79BE6F30543AE7BE2238E0DB" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C74C8DBE9E87D1E8955666E5D8D9DF2D" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
Open growth form; leaves linear or ensiform with dark coloration at base and peltate branched hairs; inflorescences bearing many flowers; flowers with a long perianth tube (1.3-3.1 mm); staminate flowers with long filaments (3.8-8.6 mm), anthers basifixed, immobile; pistillate flowers with long outer tepals (1.5-6.2 
<normalizedToken id="B64878CD232B811B5098585A20CA2EB8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.9-1.6 mm); ovary trilocular, intermediate length (2.1-4.8 mm); fruit globose or obpyriform, with few to many seeds per fruit (1-22); seeds ellipsoid or ovoid, small and narrow (1.3-2.1 
<normalizedToken id="FD53866CD8A68E49495CA6F727FACC03" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-1.1 mm); funicle short, truncate, with well-developed mucilaginous funicular hairs that adhere to the seed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CE86BB0E2D156B8630A7BB1FE2172553" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6A702D970C494E307B18476BE8BDF824" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2A1F83C11B429248D915E2AAA5D5326" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
Species published under 
<taxonomicName id="9BD574ADE8041C5CF73C8B94F80EA9DA" authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C27E78774D18757768EC746AD04F88DB" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Collospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be transferred as 
<taxonomicName id="6CFA7437DFFFC2EF173DAADB4835F9A9" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16A4BC6E946E77B60F098E20002561BD" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Astelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has nomenclatural priority. Synapomorphies recognized for the genus 
<taxonomicName id="0170333A4EE04E5825168138D396F93B" authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5F55D431B6303A50EE46B697DE2B7379" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Collospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1E9103D7B17DEAA611A00D4564578BA8" author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg 1934</bibRefCitation>
) remain valid for 
<taxonomicName id="6E76DD55F64A50AE6D50623730A7A140" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Collospermum) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="hastatum" subGenus="Collospermum" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Collospermum</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
